---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="afterlife">
  <Article
    title="afterlife"
    section="death"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      the afterlife is the idea that something continues beyond physical death.
      it appears across cultures as vision, belief, symbol, and story.
    </p>

    <p>
      rather than a single answer, it takes many forms: heaven, hell, rebirth,
      shadow worlds, ancestors, or dissolution into something larger.
    </p>

    <p>
      each version reflects not only what people believe happens after death,
      but what they value during life.
    </p>

    <h2>images of continuation</h2>

    <p>
      the afterlife often mirrors the structure of life itself. judgment,
      reward, punishment, return, or release appear in different traditions.
    </p>

    <p>
      these images are not only predictions, but symbolic expressions of
      meaning, morality, and fear.
    </p>

    <h2>the unknown</h2>

    <p>
      no system fully resolves what happens after death. even the most detailed
      visions leave space for uncertainty.
    </p>

    <p>
      this uncertainty is part of the symbol. the afterlife points beyond
      what can be confirmed.
    </p>

    <h2>psychological function</h2>

    <p>
      beliefs about the afterlife shape how people live. they can comfort,
      guide behavior, or create fear.
    </p>

    <p>
      in this way, the afterlife is not only about what comes next, but about
      how life is understood now.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death">back to death index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death/memento-mori">continue to: memento mori</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/death/grief">grief</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>
